46/*******************************************************************************
47 * Zero Bandwidth Clear
48 ******************************************************************************/
49
50static void
51gf100_gr_zbc_clear_color(struct gf100_gr *gr, int zbc)
52{
53 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
54 if (gr->zbc_color[zbc].format) {
55 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405804, gr->zbc_color[zbc].ds[0]);
56 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405808, gr->zbc_color[zbc].ds[1]);
57 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40580c, gr->zbc_color[zbc].ds[2]);
58 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405810, gr->zbc_color[zbc].ds[3]);
59 }
60 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405814, gr->zbc_color[zbc].format);
61 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405820, zbc);
62 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405824, 0x00000004); /* TRIGGER | WRITE | COLOR */
63}
64
65static int
66gf100_gr_zbc_color_get(struct gf100_gr *gr, int format,
67 const u32 ds[4], const u32 l2[4])
68{
69 struct nvkm_ltc *ltc = gr->base.engine.subdev.device->ltc;
70 int zbc = -ENOSPC, i;
71
72 for (i = ltc->zbc_min; i <= ltc->zbc_max; i++) {
73 if (gr->zbc_color[i].format) {
74 if (gr->zbc_color[i].format != format)
75 continue;
76 if (memcmp(gr->zbc_color[i].ds, ds, sizeof(
77 gr->zbc_color[i].ds)))
78 continue;
79 if (memcmp(gr->zbc_color[i].l2, l2, sizeof(
80 gr->zbc_color[i].l2))) {
81 WARN_ON(1);
82 return -EINVAL;
83 }
84 return i;
85 } else {
86 zbc = (zbc < 0) ? i : zbc;
87 }
88 }
89
90 if (zbc < 0)
91 return zbc;
92
93 memcpy(gr->zbc_color[zbc].ds, ds, sizeof(gr->zbc_color[zbc].ds));
94 memcpy(gr->zbc_color[zbc].l2, l2, sizeof(gr->zbc_color[zbc].l2));
95 gr->zbc_color[zbc].format = format;
96 nvkm_ltc_zbc_color_get(ltc, zbc, l2);
97 gf100_gr_zbc_clear_color(gr, zbc);
98 return zbc;
99}
100
101static void
102gf100_gr_zbc_clear_depth(struct gf100_gr *gr, int zbc)
103{
104 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
105 if (gr->zbc_depth[zbc].format)
106 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405818, gr->zbc_depth[zbc].ds);
107 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40581c, gr->zbc_depth[zbc].format);
108 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405820, zbc);
109 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405824, 0x00000005); /* TRIGGER | WRITE | DEPTH */
110}
111
112static int
113gf100_gr_zbc_depth_get(struct gf100_gr *gr, int format,
114 const u32 ds, const u32 l2)
115{
116 struct nvkm_ltc *ltc = gr->base.engine.subdev.device->ltc;
117 int zbc = -ENOSPC, i;
118
119 for (i = ltc->zbc_min; i <= ltc->zbc_max; i++) {
120 if (gr->zbc_depth[i].format) {
121 if (gr->zbc_depth[i].format != format)
122 continue;
123 if (gr->zbc_depth[i].ds != ds)
124 continue;
125 if (gr->zbc_depth[i].l2 != l2) {
126 WARN_ON(1);
127 return -EINVAL;
128 }
129 return i;
130 } else {
131 zbc = (zbc < 0) ? i : zbc;
132 }
133 }
134
135 if (zbc < 0)
136 return zbc;
137
138 gr->zbc_depth[zbc].format = format;
139 gr->zbc_depth[zbc].ds = ds;
140 gr->zbc_depth[zbc].l2 = l2;
141 nvkm_ltc_zbc_depth_get(ltc, zbc, l2);
142 gf100_gr_zbc_clear_depth(gr, zbc);
143 return zbc;
144}

150static int
151gf100_fermi_mthd_zbc_color(struct nvkm_object *object, void *data, u32 size)
152{
153 struct gf100_gr *gr = gf100_gr(nvkm_gr(object->engine));
154 union {
155 struct fermi_a_zbc_color_v0 v0;
156 } *args = data;
157 int ret;
158
159 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
160 switch (args->v0.format) {
161 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_ZERO:
162 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_UNORM_ONE:
163 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_RF32_GF32_BF32_AF32:
164 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_R16_G16_B16_A16:
165 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_RN16_GN16_BN16_AN16:
166 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_RS16_GS16_BS16_AS16:
167 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_RU16_GU16_BU16_AU16:
168 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_RF16_GF16_BF16_AF16:
169 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_A8R8G8B8:
170 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_A8RL8GL8BL8:
171 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_A2B10G10R10:
172 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_AU2BU10GU10RU10:
173 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_A8B8G8R8:
174 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_A8BL8GL8RL8:
175 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_AN8BN8GN8RN8:
176 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_AS8BS8GS8RS8:
177 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_AU8BU8GU8RU8:
178 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_A2R10G10B10:
179 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR_V0_FMT_BF10GF11RF11:
180 ret = gf100_gr_zbc_color_get(gr, args->v0.format,
181 args->v0.ds,
182 args->v0.l2);
183 if (ret >= 0) {
184 args->v0.index = ret;
185 return 0;
186 }
187 break;
188 default:
189 return -EINVAL;
190 }
191 }
192
193 return ret;
194}

196static int
197gf100_fermi_mthd_zbc_depth(struct nvkm_object *object, void *data, u32 size)
198{
199 struct gf100_gr *gr = gf100_gr(nvkm_gr(object->engine));
200 union {
201 struct fermi_a_zbc_depth_v0 v0;
202 } *args = data;
203 int ret;
204
205 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
206 switch (args->v0.format) {
207 case FERMI_A_ZBC_DEPTH_V0_FMT_FP32:
208 ret = gf100_gr_zbc_depth_get(gr, args->v0.format,
209 args->v0.ds,
210 args->v0.l2);
211 return (ret >= 0) ? 0 : -ENOSPC;
212 default:
213 return -EINVAL;
214 }
215 }
216
217 return ret;
218}

220static int
221gf100_fermi_mthd(struct nvkm_object *object, u32 mthd, void *data, u32 size)
222{
223 switch (mthd) {
224 case FERMI_A_ZBC_COLOR:
225 return gf100_fermi_mthd_zbc_color(object, data, size);
226 case FERMI_A_ZBC_DEPTH:
227 return gf100_fermi_mthd_zbc_depth(object, data, size);
228 default:
229 break;
230 }
231 return -EINVAL;
232}

239static void
240gf100_gr_mthd_set_shader_exceptions(struct nvkm_device *device, u32 data)
241{
242 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x419e44, data ? 0xffffffff : 0x00000000);
243 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x419e4c, data ? 0xffffffff : 0x00000000);
244}

246static bool
247gf100_gr_mthd_sw(struct nvkm_device *device, u16 class, u32 mthd, u32 data)
248{
249 switch (class & 0x00ff) {
250 case 0x97:
251 case 0xc0:
252 switch (mthd) {
253 case 0x1528:
254 gf100_gr_mthd_set_shader_exceptions(device, data);
255 return true;
256 default:
257 break;
258 }
259 break;
260 default:
261 break;
262 }
263 return false;
264}

266static int
267gf100_gr_object_get(struct nvkm_gr *base, int index, struct nvkm_sclass *sclass)
268{
269 struct gf100_gr *gr = gf100_gr(base);
270 int c = 0;
271
272 while (gr->func->sclass[c].oclass) {
273 if (c++ == index) {
274 *sclass = gr->func->sclass[index];
275 return index;
276 }
277 }
278
279 return c;
280}

282/*******************************************************************************
283 * PGRAPH context
284 ******************************************************************************/

286static int
287gf100_gr_chan_bind(struct nvkm_object *object, struct nvkm_gpuobj *parent,
288 int align, struct nvkm_gpuobj **pgpuobj)
289{
290 struct gf100_gr_chan *chan = gf100_gr_chan(object);
291 struct gf100_gr *gr = chan->gr;
292 int ret, i;
293
294 ret = nvkm_gpuobj_new(gr->base.engine.subdev.device, gr->size,
295 align, false, parent, pgpuobj);
296 if (ret)
297 return ret;
298
299 nvkm_kmap(*pgpuobj);
300 for (i = 0; i < gr->size; i += 4)
301 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, i, gr->data[i / 4]);
302
303 if (!gr->firmware) {
304 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, 0x00, chan->mmio_nr / 2);
305 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, 0x04, chan->mmio_vma.offset >> 8);
306 } else {
307 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, 0xf4, 0);
308 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, 0xf8, 0);
309 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, 0x10, chan->mmio_nr / 2);
310 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, 0x14, lower_32_bits(chan->mmio_vma.offset));
311 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, 0x18, upper_32_bits(chan->mmio_vma.offset));
312 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, 0x1c, 1);
313 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, 0x20, 0);
314 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, 0x28, 0);
315 nvkm_wo32(*pgpuobj, 0x2c, 0);
316 }
317 nvkm_done(*pgpuobj);
318 return 0;
319}

321static void *
322gf100_gr_chan_dtor(struct nvkm_object *object)
323{
324 struct gf100_gr_chan *chan = gf100_gr_chan(object);
325 int i;
326
327 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(chan->data); i++) {
328 if (chan->data[i].vma.node) {
329 nvkm_vm_unmap(&chan->data[i].vma);
330 nvkm_vm_put(&chan->data[i].vma);
331 }
332 nvkm_memory_del(&chan->data[i].mem);
333 }
334
335 if (chan->mmio_vma.node) {
336 nvkm_vm_unmap(&chan->mmio_vma);
337 nvkm_vm_put(&chan->mmio_vma);
338 }
339 nvkm_memory_del(&chan->mmio);
340 return chan;
341}

343static const struct nvkm_object_func
344gf100_gr_chan = {
345 .dtor = gf100_gr_chan_dtor,
346 .bind = gf100_gr_chan_bind,
347};
348
349static int
350gf100_gr_chan_new(struct nvkm_gr *base, struct nvkm_fifo_chan *fifoch,
351 const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
352 struct nvkm_object **pobject)
353{
354 struct gf100_gr *gr = gf100_gr(base);
355 struct gf100_gr_data *data = gr->mmio_data;
356 struct gf100_gr_mmio *mmio = gr->mmio_list;
357 struct gf100_gr_chan *chan;
358 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
359 int ret, i;
360
361 if (!(chan = kzalloc(sizeof(*chan), GFP_KERNEL)))
362 return -ENOMEM;
363 nvkm_object_ctor(&gf100_gr_chan, oclass, &chan->object);
364 chan->gr = gr;
365 *pobject = &chan->object;
366
367 /* allocate memory for a "mmio list" buffer that's used by the HUB
368 * fuc to modify some per-context register settings on first load
369 * of the context.
370 */
371 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST, 0x1000, 0x100,
372 false, &chan->mmio);
373 if (ret)
374 return ret;
375
376 ret = nvkm_vm_get(fifoch->vm, 0x1000, 12, NV_MEM_ACCESS_RW |
377 NV_MEM_ACCESS_SYS, &chan->mmio_vma);
378 if (ret)
379 return ret;
380
381 nvkm_memory_map(chan->mmio, &chan->mmio_vma, 0);
382
383 /* allocate buffers referenced by mmio list */
384 for (i = 0; data->size && i < ARRAY_SIZE(gr->mmio_data); i++) {
385 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST,
386 data->size, data->align, false,
387 &chan->data[i].mem);
388 if (ret)
389 return ret;
390
391 ret = nvkm_vm_get(fifoch->vm,
392 nvkm_memory_size(chan->data[i].mem), 12,
393 data->access, &chan->data[i].vma);
394 if (ret)
395 return ret;
396
397 nvkm_memory_map(chan->data[i].mem, &chan->data[i].vma, 0);
398 data++;
399 }
400
401 /* finally, fill in the mmio list and point the context at it */
402 nvkm_kmap(chan->mmio);
403 for (i = 0; mmio->addr && i < ARRAY_SIZE(gr->mmio_list); i++) {
404 u32 addr = mmio->addr;
405 u32 data = mmio->data;
406
407 if (mmio->buffer >= 0) {
408 u64 info = chan->data[mmio->buffer].vma.offset;
409 data |= info >> mmio->shift;
410 }
411
412 nvkm_wo32(chan->mmio, chan->mmio_nr++ * 4, addr);
413 nvkm_wo32(chan->mmio, chan->mmio_nr++ * 4, data);
414 mmio++;
415 }
416 nvkm_done(chan->mmio);
417 return 0;
418}

680void
681gf100_gr_zbc_init(struct gf100_gr *gr)
682{
683 const u32 zero[] = { 0x00000000, 0x00000000, 0x00000000, 0x00000000,
684 0x00000000, 0x00000000, 0x00000000, 0x00000000 };
685 const u32 one[] = { 0x3f800000, 0x3f800000, 0x3f800000, 0x3f800000,
686 0xffffffff, 0xffffffff, 0xffffffff, 0xffffffff };
687 const u32 f32_0[] = { 0x00000000, 0x00000000, 0x00000000, 0x00000000,
688 0x00000000, 0x00000000, 0x00000000, 0x00000000 };
689 const u32 f32_1[] = { 0x3f800000, 0x3f800000, 0x3f800000, 0x3f800000,
690 0x3f800000, 0x3f800000, 0x3f800000, 0x3f800000 };
691 struct nvkm_ltc *ltc = gr->base.engine.subdev.device->ltc;
692 int index;
693
694 if (!gr->zbc_color[0].format) {
695 gf100_gr_zbc_color_get(gr, 1, & zero[0], &zero[4]);
696 gf100_gr_zbc_color_get(gr, 2, & one[0], &one[4]);
697 gf100_gr_zbc_color_get(gr, 4, &f32_0[0], &f32_0[4]);
698 gf100_gr_zbc_color_get(gr, 4, &f32_1[0], &f32_1[4]);
699 gf100_gr_zbc_depth_get(gr, 1, 0x00000000, 0x00000000);
700 gf100_gr_zbc_depth_get(gr, 1, 0x3f800000, 0x3f800000);
701 }
702
703 for (index = ltc->zbc_min; index <= ltc->zbc_max; index++)
704 gf100_gr_zbc_clear_color(gr, index);
705 for (index = ltc->zbc_min; index <= ltc->zbc_max; index++)
706 gf100_gr_zbc_clear_depth(gr, index);
707}

709/**
710 * Wait until GR goes idle. GR is considered idle if it is disabled by the
711 * MC (0x200) register, or GR is not busy and a context switch is not in
712 * progress.
713 */
714int
715gf100_gr_wait_idle(struct gf100_gr *gr)
716{
717 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
718 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
719 unsigned long end_jiffies = jiffies + msecs_to_jiffies(2000);
720 bool gr_enabled, ctxsw_active, gr_busy;
721
722 do {
723 /*
724 * required to make sure FIFO_ENGINE_STATUS (0x2640) is
725 * up-to-date
726 */
727 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400700);
728
729 gr_enabled = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x200) & 0x1000;
730 ctxsw_active = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x2640) & 0x8000;
731 gr_busy = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x40060c) & 0x1;
732
733 if (!gr_enabled || (!gr_busy && !ctxsw_active))
734 return 0;
735 } while (time_before(jiffies, end_jiffies));
736
737 nvkm_error(subdev,
738 "wait for idle timeout (en: %d, ctxsw: %d, busy: %d)\n",
739 gr_enabled, ctxsw_active, gr_busy);
740 return -EAGAIN;
741}

743void
744gf100_gr_mmio(struct gf100_gr *gr, const struct gf100_gr_pack *p)
745{
746 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
747 const struct gf100_gr_pack *pack;
748 const struct gf100_gr_init *init;
749
750 pack_for_each_init(init, pack, p) {
751 u32 next = init->addr + init->count * init->pitch;
752 u32 addr = init->addr;
753 while (addr < next) {
754 nvkm_wr32(device, addr, init->data);
755 addr += init->pitch;
756 }
757 }
758}

760void
761gf100_gr_icmd(struct gf100_gr *gr, const struct gf100_gr_pack *p)
762{
763 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
764 const struct gf100_gr_pack *pack;
765 const struct gf100_gr_init *init;
766 u32 data = 0;
767
768 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400208, 0x80000000);
769
770 pack_for_each_init(init, pack, p) {
771 u32 next = init->addr + init->count * init->pitch;
772 u32 addr = init->addr;
773
774 if ((pack == p && init == p->init) || data != init->data) {
775 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400204, init->data);
776 data = init->data;
777 }
778
779 while (addr < next) {
780 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400200, addr);
781 /**
782 * Wait for GR to go idle after submitting a
783 * GO_IDLE bundle
784 */
785 if ((addr & 0xffff) == 0xe100)
786 gf100_gr_wait_idle(gr);
787 nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
788 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400700) & 0x00000004))
789 break;
790 );
791 addr += init->pitch;
792 }
793 }
794
795 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400208, 0x00000000);
796}

798void
799gf100_gr_mthd(struct gf100_gr *gr, const struct gf100_gr_pack *p)
800{
801 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
802 const struct gf100_gr_pack *pack;
803 const struct gf100_gr_init *init;
804 u32 data = 0;
805
806 pack_for_each_init(init, pack, p) {
807 u32 ctrl = 0x80000000 | pack->type;
808 u32 next = init->addr + init->count * init->pitch;
809 u32 addr = init->addr;
810
811 if ((pack == p && init == p->init) || data != init->data) {
812 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40448c, init->data);
813 data = init->data;
814 }
815
816 while (addr < next) {
817 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x404488, ctrl | (addr << 14));
818 addr += init->pitch;
819 }
820 }
821}

923gf100_gr_trap_mp(struct gf100_gr *gr, int gpc, int tpc)

937 gpc, tpc, gerr, glob, werr, warp ? warp->name : "");

940 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x650), gerr);

943static void
944gf100_gr_trap_tpc(struct gf100_gr *gr, int gpc, int tpc)
945{
946 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
947 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
948 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x0508));
949
950 if (stat & 0x00000001) {
951 u32 trap = nvkm_rd32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x0224));
952 nvkm_error(subdev, "GPC%d/TPC%d/TEX: %08x\n", gpc, tpc, trap);
953 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x0224), 0xc0000000);
954 stat &= ~0x00000001;
955 }
956
957 if (stat & 0x00000002) {
958 gf100_gr_trap_mp(gr, gpc, tpc);
959 stat &= ~0x00000002;
960 }
961
962 if (stat & 0x00000004) {
963 u32 trap = nvkm_rd32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x0084));
964 nvkm_error(subdev, "GPC%d/TPC%d/POLY: %08x\n", gpc, tpc, trap);
965 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x0084), 0xc0000000);
966 stat &= ~0x00000004;
967 }
968
969 if (stat & 0x00000008) {
970 u32 trap = nvkm_rd32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x048c));
971 nvkm_error(subdev, "GPC%d/TPC%d/L1C: %08x\n", gpc, tpc, trap);
972 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x048c), 0xc0000000);
973 stat &= ~0x00000008;
974 }
975
976 if (stat) {
977 nvkm_error(subdev, "GPC%d/TPC%d/%08x: unknown\n", gpc, tpc, stat);
978 }
979}

981static void
982gf100_gr_trap_gpc(struct gf100_gr *gr, int gpc)
983{
984 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
985 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
986 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x2c90));
987 int tpc;
988
989 if (stat & 0x00000001) {
990 gf100_gr_trap_gpc_rop(gr, gpc);
991 stat &= ~0x00000001;
992 }
993
994 if (stat & 0x00000002) {
995 u32 trap = nvkm_rd32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0900));
996 nvkm_error(subdev, "GPC%d/ZCULL: %08x\n", gpc, trap);
997 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0900), 0xc0000000);
998 stat &= ~0x00000002;
999 }
1000
1001 if (stat & 0x00000004) {
1002 u32 trap = nvkm_rd32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x1028));
1003 nvkm_error(subdev, "GPC%d/CCACHE: %08x\n", gpc, trap);
1004 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x1028), 0xc0000000);
1005 stat &= ~0x00000004;
1006 }
1007
1008 if (stat & 0x00000008) {
1009 u32 trap = nvkm_rd32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0824));
1010 nvkm_error(subdev, "GPC%d/ESETUP: %08x\n", gpc, trap);
1011 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0824), 0xc0000000);
1012 stat &= ~0x00000009;
1013 }
1014
1015 for (tpc = 0; tpc < gr->tpc_nr[gpc]; tpc++) {
1016 u32 mask = 0x00010000 << tpc;
1017 if (stat & mask) {
1018 gf100_gr_trap_tpc(gr, gpc, tpc);
1019 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x2c90), mask);
1020 stat &= ~mask;
1021 }
1022 }
1023
1024 if (stat) {
1025 nvkm_error(subdev, "GPC%d/%08x: unknown\n", gpc, stat);
1026 }
1027}

1029static void
1030gf100_gr_trap_intr(struct gf100_gr *gr)
1031{
1032 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
1033 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
1034 u32 trap = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400108);
1035 int rop, gpc;
1036
1037 if (trap & 0x00000001) {
1038 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x404000);
1039 nvkm_error(subdev, "DISPATCH %08x\n", stat);
1040 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x404000, 0xc0000000);
1041 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x00000001);
1042 trap &= ~0x00000001;
1043 }
1044
1045 if (trap & 0x00000002) {
1046 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x404600);
1047 nvkm_error(subdev, "M2MF %08x\n", stat);
1048 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x404600, 0xc0000000);
1049 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x00000002);
1050 trap &= ~0x00000002;
1051 }
1052
1053 if (trap & 0x00000008) {
1054 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x408030);
1055 nvkm_error(subdev, "CCACHE %08x\n", stat);
1056 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x408030, 0xc0000000);
1057 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x00000008);
1058 trap &= ~0x00000008;
1059 }
1060
1061 if (trap & 0x00000010) {
1062 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x405840);
1063 nvkm_error(subdev, "SHADER %08x\n", stat);
1064 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405840, 0xc0000000);
1065 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x00000010);
1066 trap &= ~0x00000010;
1067 }
1068
1069 if (trap & 0x00000040) {
1070 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x40601c);
1071 nvkm_error(subdev, "UNK6 %08x\n", stat);
1072 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40601c, 0xc0000000);
1073 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x00000040);
1074 trap &= ~0x00000040;
1075 }
1076
1077 if (trap & 0x00000080) {
1078 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x404490);
1079 nvkm_error(subdev, "MACRO %08x\n", stat);
1080 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x404490, 0xc0000000);
1081 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x00000080);
1082 trap &= ~0x00000080;
1083 }
1084
1085 if (trap & 0x00000100) {
1086 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x407020) & 0x3fffffff;
1087 char sked[128];
1088
1089 nvkm_snprintbf(sked, sizeof(sked), gk104_sked_error, stat);
1090 nvkm_error(subdev, "SKED: %08x [%s]\n", stat, sked);
1091
1092 if (stat)
1093 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x407020, 0x40000000);
1094 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x00000100);
1095 trap &= ~0x00000100;
1096 }
1097
1098 if (trap & 0x01000000) {
1099 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400118);
1100 for (gpc = 0; stat && gpc < gr->gpc_nr; gpc++) {
1101 u32 mask = 0x00000001 << gpc;
1102 if (stat & mask) {
1103 gf100_gr_trap_gpc(gr, gpc);
1104 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400118, mask);
1105 stat &= ~mask;
1106 }
1107 }
1108 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x01000000);
1109 trap &= ~0x01000000;
1110 }
1111
1112 if (trap & 0x02000000) {
1113 for (rop = 0; rop < gr->rop_nr; rop++) {
1114 u32 statz = nvkm_rd32(device, ROP_UNIT(rop, 0x070));
1115 u32 statc = nvkm_rd32(device, ROP_UNIT(rop, 0x144));
1116 nvkm_error(subdev, "ROP%d %08x %08x\n",
1117 rop, statz, statc);
1118 nvkm_wr32(device, ROP_UNIT(rop, 0x070), 0xc0000000);
1119 nvkm_wr32(device, ROP_UNIT(rop, 0x144), 0xc0000000);
1120 }
1121 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0x02000000);
1122 trap &= ~0x02000000;
1123 }
1124
1125 if (trap) {
1126 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP UNHANDLED %08x\n", trap);
1127 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, trap);
1128 }
1129}

1150void
1151gf100_gr_ctxctl_debug(struct gf100_gr *gr)
1152{
1153 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
1154 u32 gpcnr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409604) & 0xffff;

1157 gf100_gr_ctxctl_debug_unit(gr, 0x409000);
1158 for (gpc = 0; gpc < gpcnr; gpc++)
1159 gf100_gr_ctxctl_debug_unit(gr, 0x502000 + (gpc * 0x8000));
1160}
1161
1162static void
1163gf100_gr_ctxctl_isr(struct gf100_gr *gr)
1164{
1165 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
1166 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
1167 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409c18);
1168
1169 if (stat & 0x00000001) {
1170 u32 code = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409814);
1171 if (code == E_BAD_FWMTHD) {
1172 u32 class = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409808);
1173 u32 addr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x40980c);
1174 u32 subc = (addr & 0x00070000) >> 16;
1175 u32 mthd = (addr & 0x00003ffc);
1176 u32 data = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409810);
1177
1178 nvkm_error(subdev, "FECS MTHD subc %d class %04x "
1179 "mthd %04x data %08x\n",
1180 subc, class, mthd, data);
1181
1182 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409c20, 0x00000001);
1183 stat &= ~0x00000001;
1184 } else {
1185 nvkm_error(subdev, "FECS ucode error %d\n", code);
1186 }
1187 }
1188
1189 if (stat & 0x00080000) {
1190 nvkm_error(subdev, "FECS watchdog timeout\n");
1191 gf100_gr_ctxctl_debug(gr);
1192 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409c20, 0x00080000);
1193 stat &= ~0x00080000;
1194 }
1195
1196 if (stat) {
1197 nvkm_error(subdev, "FECS %08x\n", stat);
1198 gf100_gr_ctxctl_debug(gr);
1199 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409c20, stat);
1200 }
1201}
1202
1203static void
1204gf100_gr_intr(struct nvkm_gr *base)
1205{
1206 struct gf100_gr *gr = gf100_gr(base);
1207 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
1208 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
1209 struct nvkm_fifo_chan *chan;
1210 unsigned long flags;
1211 u64 inst = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409b00) & 0x0fffffff;
1212 u32 stat = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400100);
1213 u32 addr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400704);
1214 u32 mthd = (addr & 0x00003ffc);
1215 u32 subc = (addr & 0x00070000) >> 16;
1216 u32 data = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400708);
1217 u32 code = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400110);
1218 u32 class;
1219 const char *name = "unknown";
1220 int chid = -1;
1221
1222 chan = nvkm_fifo_chan_inst(device->fifo, (u64)inst << 12, &flags);
1223 if (chan) {
1224 name = chan->object.client->name;
1225 chid = chan->chid;
1226 }
1227
1228 if (device->card_type < NV_E0 || subc < 4)
1229 class = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x404200 + (subc * 4));
1230 else
1231 class = 0x0000;
1232
1233 if (stat & 0x00000001) {
1234 /*
1235 * notifier interrupt, only needed for cyclestats
1236 * can be safely ignored
1237 */
1238 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400100, 0x00000001);
1239 stat &= ~0x00000001;
1240 }
1241
1242 if (stat & 0x00000010) {
1243 if (!gf100_gr_mthd_sw(device, class, mthd, data)) {
1244 nvkm_error(subdev, "ILLEGAL_MTHD ch %d [%010"PRIx64" %s] "
1245 "subc %d class %04x mthd %04x data %08x\n",
1246 chid, inst << 12, name, subc,
1247 class, mthd, data);
1248 }
1249 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400100, 0x00000010);
1250 stat &= ~0x00000010;
1251 }
1252
1253 if (stat & 0x00000020) {
1254 nvkm_error(subdev, "ILLEGAL_CLASS ch %d [%010"PRIx64" %s] "
1255 "subc %d class %04x mthd %04x data %08x\n",
1256 chid, inst << 12, name, subc, class, mthd, data);
1257 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400100, 0x00000020);
1258 stat &= ~0x00000020;
1259 }
1260
1261 if (stat & 0x00100000) {
1262 const struct nvkm_enum *en =
1263 nvkm_enum_find(nv50_data_error_names, code);
1264 nvkm_error(subdev, "DATA_ERROR %08x [%s] ch %d [%010"PRIx64" %s] "
1265 "subc %d class %04x mthd %04x data %08x\n",
1266 code, en ? en->name : "", chid, inst << 12,
1267 name, subc, class, mthd, data);
1268 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400100, 0x00100000);
1269 stat &= ~0x00100000;
1270 }
1271
1272 if (stat & 0x00200000) {
1273 nvkm_error(subdev, "TRAP ch %d [%010"PRIx64" %s]\n",
1274 chid, inst << 12, name);
1275 gf100_gr_trap_intr(gr);
1276 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400100, 0x00200000);
1277 stat &= ~0x00200000;
1278 }
1279
1280 if (stat & 0x00080000) {
1281 gf100_gr_ctxctl_isr(gr);
1282 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400100, 0x00080000);
1283 stat &= ~0x00080000;
1284 }
1285
1286 if (stat) {
1287 nvkm_error(subdev, "intr %08x\n", stat);
1288 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400100, stat);
1289 }
1290
1291 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400500, 0x00010001);
1292 nvkm_fifo_chan_put(device->fifo, flags, &chan);
1293}

1295static void
1296gf100_gr_init_fw(struct gf100_gr *gr, u32 fuc_base,
1297 struct gf100_gr_fuc *code, struct gf100_gr_fuc *data)
1298{
1299 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
1300 int i;
1301
1302 nvkm_wr32(device, fuc_base + 0x01c0, 0x01000000);
1303 for (i = 0; i < data->size / 4; i++)
1304 nvkm_wr32(device, fuc_base + 0x01c4, data->data[i]);
1305
1306 nvkm_wr32(device, fuc_base + 0x0180, 0x01000000);
1307 for (i = 0; i < code->size / 4; i++) {
1308 if ((i & 0x3f) == 0)
1309 nvkm_wr32(device, fuc_base + 0x0188, i >> 6);
1310 nvkm_wr32(device, fuc_base + 0x0184, code->data[i]);
1311 }
1312
1313 /* code must be padded to 0x40 words */
1314 for (; i & 0x3f; i++)
1315 nvkm_wr32(device, fuc_base + 0x0184, 0);
1316}
1317
1318static void
1319gf100_gr_init_csdata(struct gf100_gr *gr,
1320 const struct gf100_gr_pack *pack,
1321 u32 falcon, u32 starstar, u32 base)
1322{
1323 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
1324 const struct gf100_gr_pack *iter;
1325 const struct gf100_gr_init *init;
1326 u32 addr = ~0, prev = ~0, xfer = 0;
1327 u32 star, temp;
1328
1329 nvkm_wr32(device, falcon + 0x01c0, 0x02000000 + starstar);
1330 star = nvkm_rd32(device, falcon + 0x01c4);
1331 temp = nvkm_rd32(device, falcon + 0x01c4);
1332 if (temp > star)
1333 star = temp;
1334 nvkm_wr32(device, falcon + 0x01c0, 0x01000000 + star);
1335
1336 pack_for_each_init(init, iter, pack) {
1337 u32 head = init->addr - base;
1338 u32 tail = head + init->count * init->pitch;
1339 while (head < tail) {
1340 if (head != prev + 4 || xfer >= 32) {
1341 if (xfer) {
1342 u32 data = ((--xfer << 26) | addr);
1343 nvkm_wr32(device, falcon + 0x01c4, data);
1344 star += 4;
1345 }
1346 addr = head;
1347 xfer = 0;
1348 }
1349 prev = head;
1350 xfer = xfer + 1;
1351 head = head + init->pitch;
1352 }
1353 }
1354
1355 nvkm_wr32(device, falcon + 0x01c4, (--xfer << 26) | addr);
1356 nvkm_wr32(device, falcon + 0x01c0, 0x01000004 + starstar);
1357 nvkm_wr32(device, falcon + 0x01c4, star + 4);
1358}

1360int
1361gf100_gr_init_ctxctl(struct gf100_gr *gr)
1362{
1363 const struct gf100_grctx_func *grctx = gr->func->grctx;
1364 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
1365 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
1366 int i;
1367
1368 if (gr->firmware) {
1369 /* load fuc microcode */
1370 nvkm_mc_unk260(device->mc, 0);
1371 gf100_gr_init_fw(gr, 0x409000, &gr->fuc409c, &gr->fuc409d);
1372 gf100_gr_init_fw(gr, 0x41a000, &gr->fuc41ac, &gr->fuc41ad);
1373 nvkm_mc_unk260(device->mc, 1);
1374
1375 /* start both of them running */
1376 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409840, 0xffffffff);
1377 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x41a10c, 0x00000000);
1378 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40910c, 0x00000000);
1379 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x41a100, 0x00000002);
1380 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409100, 0x00000002);
1381 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
1382 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409800) & 0x00000001)
1383 break;
1384 ) < 0)
1385 return -EBUSY;
1386
1387 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409840, 0xffffffff);
1388 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409500, 0x7fffffff);
1389 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409504, 0x00000021);
1390
1391 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409840, 0xffffffff);
1392 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409500, 0x00000000);
1393 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409504, 0x00000010);
1394 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
1395 if ((gr->size = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409800)))
1396 break;
1397 ) < 0)
1398 return -EBUSY;
1399
1400 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409840, 0xffffffff);
1401 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409500, 0x00000000);
1402 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409504, 0x00000016);
1403 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
1404 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409800))
1405 break;
1406 ) < 0)
1407 return -EBUSY;
1408
1409 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409840, 0xffffffff);
1410 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409500, 0x00000000);
1411 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409504, 0x00000025);
1412 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
1413 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409800))
1414 break;
1415 ) < 0)
1416 return -EBUSY;
1417
1418 if (device->chipset >= 0xe0) {
1419 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409800, 0x00000000);
1420 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409500, 0x00000001);
1421 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409504, 0x00000030);
1422 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
1423 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409800))
1424 break;
1425 ) < 0)
1426 return -EBUSY;
1427
1428 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409810, 0xb00095c8);
1429 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409800, 0x00000000);
1430 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409500, 0x00000001);
1431 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409504, 0x00000031);
1432 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
1433 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409800))
1434 break;
1435 ) < 0)
1436 return -EBUSY;
1437
1438 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409810, 0x00080420);
1439 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409800, 0x00000000);
1440 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409500, 0x00000001);
1441 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409504, 0x00000032);
1442 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
1443 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409800))
1444 break;
1445 ) < 0)
1446 return -EBUSY;
1447
1448 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409614, 0x00000070);
1449 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409614, 0x00000770);
1450 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40802c, 0x00000001);
1451 }
1452
1453 if (gr->data == NULL) {
1454 int ret = gf100_grctx_generate(gr);
1455 if (ret) {
1456 nvkm_error(subdev, "failed to construct context\n");
1457 return ret;
1458 }
1459 }
1460
1461 return 0;
1462 } else
1463 if (!gr->func->fecs.ucode) {
1464 return -ENOSYS;
1465 }
1466
1467 /* load HUB microcode */
1468 nvkm_mc_unk260(device->mc, 0);
1469 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4091c0, 0x01000000);
1470 for (i = 0; i < gr->func->fecs.ucode->data.size / 4; i++)
1471 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x4091c4, gr->func->fecs.ucode->data.data[i]);
1472
1473 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409180, 0x01000000);
1474 for (i = 0; i < gr->func->fecs.ucode->code.size / 4; i++) {
1475 if ((i & 0x3f) == 0)
1476 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409188, i >> 6);
1477 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409184, gr->func->fecs.ucode->code.data[i]);
1478 }
1479
1480 /* load GPC microcode */
1481 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x41a1c0, 0x01000000);
1482 for (i = 0; i < gr->func->gpccs.ucode->data.size / 4; i++)
1483 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x41a1c4, gr->func->gpccs.ucode->data.data[i]);
1484
1485 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x41a180, 0x01000000);
1486 for (i = 0; i < gr->func->gpccs.ucode->code.size / 4; i++) {
1487 if ((i & 0x3f) == 0)
1488 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x41a188, i >> 6);
1489 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x41a184, gr->func->gpccs.ucode->code.data[i]);
1490 }
1491 nvkm_mc_unk260(device->mc, 1);
1492
1493 /* load register lists */
1494 gf100_gr_init_csdata(gr, grctx->hub, 0x409000, 0x000, 0x000000);
1495 gf100_gr_init_csdata(gr, grctx->gpc, 0x41a000, 0x000, 0x418000);
1496 gf100_gr_init_csdata(gr, grctx->tpc, 0x41a000, 0x004, 0x419800);
1497 gf100_gr_init_csdata(gr, grctx->ppc, 0x41a000, 0x008, 0x41be00);
1498
1499 /* start HUB ucode running, it'll init the GPCs */
1500 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40910c, 0x00000000);
1501 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409100, 0x00000002);
1502 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
1503 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409800) & 0x80000000)
1504 break;
1505 ) < 0) {
1506 gf100_gr_ctxctl_debug(gr);
1507 return -EBUSY;
1508 }
1509
1510 gr->size = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409804);
1511 if (gr->data == NULL) {
1512 int ret = gf100_grctx_generate(gr);
1513 if (ret) {
1514 nvkm_error(subdev, "failed to construct context\n");
1515 return ret;
1516 }
1517 }
1518
1519 return 0;
1520}

1522static int
1523gf100_gr_oneinit(struct nvkm_gr *base)
1524{
1525 struct gf100_gr *gr = gf100_gr(base);
1526 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
1527 int ret, i, j;
1528
1529 nvkm_pmu_pgob(device->pmu, false);
1530
1531 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST, 0x1000, 256, false,
1532 &gr->unk4188b4);
1533 if (ret)
1534 return ret;
1535
1536 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST, 0x1000, 256, false,
1537 &gr->unk4188b8);
1538 if (ret)
1539 return ret;
1540
1541 nvkm_kmap(gr->unk4188b4);
1542 for (i = 0; i < 0x1000; i += 4)
1543 nvkm_wo32(gr->unk4188b4, i, 0x00000010);
1544 nvkm_done(gr->unk4188b4);
1545
1546 nvkm_kmap(gr->unk4188b8);
1547 for (i = 0; i < 0x1000; i += 4)
1548 nvkm_wo32(gr->unk4188b8, i, 0x00000010);
1549 nvkm_done(gr->unk4188b8);
1550
1551 gr->rop_nr = (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409604) & 0x001f0000) >> 16;
1552 gr->gpc_nr = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x409604) & 0x0000001f;
1553 for (i = 0; i < gr->gpc_nr; i++) {
1554 gr->tpc_nr[i] = nvkm_rd32(device, GPC_UNIT(i, 0x2608));
1555 gr->tpc_total += gr->tpc_nr[i];
1556 gr->ppc_nr[i] = gr->func->ppc_nr;
1557 for (j = 0; j < gr->ppc_nr[i]; j++) {
1558 u8 mask = nvkm_rd32(device, GPC_UNIT(i, 0x0c30 + (j * 4)));
1559 if (mask)
1560 gr->ppc_mask[i] |= (1 << j);
1561 gr->ppc_tpc_nr[i][j] = hweight8(mask);
1562 }
1563 }
1564
1565 /*XXX: these need figuring out... though it might not even matter */
1566 switch (device->chipset) {
1567 case 0xc0:
1568 if (gr->tpc_total == 11) { /* 465, 3/4/4/0, 4 */
1569 gr->magic_not_rop_nr = 0x07;
1570 } else
1571 if (gr->tpc_total == 14) { /* 470, 3/3/4/4, 5 */
1572 gr->magic_not_rop_nr = 0x05;
1573 } else
1574 if (gr->tpc_total == 15) { /* 480, 3/4/4/4, 6 */
1575 gr->magic_not_rop_nr = 0x06;
1576 }
1577 break;
1578 case 0xc3: /* 450, 4/0/0/0, 2 */
1579 gr->magic_not_rop_nr = 0x03;
1580 break;
1581 case 0xc4: /* 460, 3/4/0/0, 4 */
1582 gr->magic_not_rop_nr = 0x01;
1583 break;
1584 case 0xc1: /* 2/0/0/0, 1 */
1585 gr->magic_not_rop_nr = 0x01;
1586 break;
1587 case 0xc8: /* 4/4/3/4, 5 */
1588 gr->magic_not_rop_nr = 0x06;
1589 break;
1590 case 0xce: /* 4/4/0/0, 4 */
1591 gr->magic_not_rop_nr = 0x03;
1592 break;
1593 case 0xcf: /* 4/0/0/0, 3 */
1594 gr->magic_not_rop_nr = 0x03;
1595 break;
1596 case 0xd7:
1597 case 0xd9: /* 1/0/0/0, 1 */
1598 case 0xea: /* gk20a */
1599 case 0x12b: /* gm20b */
1600 gr->magic_not_rop_nr = 0x01;
1601 break;
1602 }
1603
1604 return 0;
1605}

1652int
1653gf100_gr_ctor_fw(struct gf100_gr *gr, const char *fwname,
1654 struct gf100_gr_fuc *fuc)
1655{
1656 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
1657 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
1658 const struct firmware *fw;
1659 char f[64];
1660 char cname[16];
1661 int ret;
1662 int i;
1663
1664 /* Convert device name to lowercase */
1665 strncpy(cname, device->chip->name, sizeof(cname));
1666 cname[sizeof(cname) - 1] = '\0';
1667 i = strlen(cname);
1668 while (i) {
1669 --i;
1670 cname[i] = tolower(cname[i]);
1671 }
1672
1673 snprintf(f, sizeof(f), "nvidia/%s/%s.bin", cname, fwname);
1674 ret = request_firmware(&fw, f, device->dev);
1675 if (ret) {
1676 nvkm_error(subdev, "failed to load %s\n", fwname);
1677 return ret;
1678 }
1679
1680 fuc->size = fw->size;
1681 fuc->data = kmemdup(fw->data, fuc->size, GFP_KERNEL);
1682 release_firmware(fw);
1683 return (fuc->data != NULL) ? 0 : -ENOMEM;
1684}

1686int
1687gf100_gr_ctor(const struct gf100_gr_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
1688 int index, struct gf100_gr *gr)
1689{
1690 int ret;
1691
1692 gr->func = func;
1693 gr->firmware = nvkm_boolopt(device->cfgopt, "NvGrUseFW",
1694 func->fecs.ucode == NULL);
1695
1696 ret = nvkm_gr_ctor(&gf100_gr_, device, index, 0x08001000,
1697 gr->firmware || func->fecs.ucode != NULL,
1698 &gr->base);
1699 if (ret)
1700 return ret;
1701
1702 if (gr->firmware) {
1703 nvkm_info(&gr->base.engine.subdev, "using external firmware\n");
1704 if (gf100_gr_ctor_fw(gr, "fecs_inst", &gr->fuc409c) ||
1705 gf100_gr_ctor_fw(gr, "fecs_data", &gr->fuc409d) ||
1706 gf100_gr_ctor_fw(gr, "gpccs_inst", &gr->fuc41ac) ||
1707 gf100_gr_ctor_fw(gr, "gpccs_data", &gr->fuc41ad))
1708 return -ENODEV;
1709 }
1710
1711 return 0;
1712}

1725int
1726gf100_gr_init(struct gf100_gr *gr)
1727{
1728 struct nvkm_device *device = gr->base.engine.subdev.device;
1729 const u32 magicgpc918 = DIV_ROUND_UP(0x00800000, gr->tpc_total);
1730 u32 data[TPC_MAX / 8] = {};
1731 u8 tpcnr[GPC_MAX];
1732 int gpc, tpc, rop;
1733 int i;
1734
1735 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0880), 0x00000000);
1736 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x08a4), 0x00000000);
1737 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0888), 0x00000000);
1738 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x088c), 0x00000000);
1739 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0890), 0x00000000);
1740 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0894), 0x00000000);
1741 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x08b4), nvkm_memory_addr(gr->unk4188b4) >> 8);
1742 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x08b8), nvkm_memory_addr(gr->unk4188b8) >> 8);
1743
1744 gf100_gr_mmio(gr, gr->func->mmio);
1745
1746 nvkm_mask(device, TPC_UNIT(0, 0, 0x05c), 0x00000001, 0x00000001);
1747
1748 memcpy(tpcnr, gr->tpc_nr, sizeof(gr->tpc_nr));
1749 for (i = 0, gpc = -1; i < gr->tpc_total; i++) {
1750 do {
1751 gpc = (gpc + 1) % gr->gpc_nr;
1752 } while (!tpcnr[gpc]);
1753 tpc = gr->tpc_nr[gpc] - tpcnr[gpc]--;
1754
1755 data[i / 8] |= tpc << ((i % 8) * 4);
1756 }
1757
1758 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0980), data[0]);
1759 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0984), data[1]);
1760 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x0988), data[2]);
1761 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x098c), data[3]);
1762
1763 for (gpc = 0; gpc < gr->gpc_nr; gpc++) {
1764 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0914),
1765 gr->magic_not_rop_nr << 8 | gr->tpc_nr[gpc]);
1766 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0910), 0x00040000 |
1767 gr->tpc_total);
1768 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0918), magicgpc918);
1769 }
1770
1771 if (device->chipset != 0xd7)
1772 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x1bd4), magicgpc918);
1773 else
1774 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x3fd4), magicgpc918);
1775
1776 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_BCAST(0x08ac), nvkm_rd32(device, 0x100800));
1777
1778 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400500, 0x00010001);
1779
1780 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400100, 0xffffffff);
1781 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40013c, 0xffffffff);
1782
1783 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x409c24, 0x000f0000);
1784 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x404000, 0xc0000000);
1785 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x404600, 0xc0000000);
1786 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x408030, 0xc0000000);
1787 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40601c, 0xc0000000);
1788 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x404490, 0xc0000000);
1789 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x406018, 0xc0000000);
1790 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405840, 0xc0000000);
1791 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x405844, 0x00ffffff);
1792 nvkm_mask(device, 0x419cc0, 0x00000008, 0x00000008);
1793 nvkm_mask(device, 0x419eb4, 0x00001000, 0x00001000);
1794
1795 for (gpc = 0; gpc < gr->gpc_nr; gpc++) {
1796 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0420), 0xc0000000);
1797 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0900), 0xc0000000);
1798 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x1028), 0xc0000000);
1799 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x0824), 0xc0000000);
1800 for (tpc = 0; tpc < gr->tpc_nr[gpc]; tpc++) {
1801 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x508), 0xffffffff);
1802 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x50c), 0xffffffff);
1803 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x224), 0xc0000000);
1804 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x48c), 0xc0000000);
1805 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x084), 0xc0000000);
1806 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x644), 0x001ffffe);
1807 nvkm_wr32(device, TPC_UNIT(gpc, tpc, 0x64c), 0x0000000f);
1808 }
1809 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x2c90), 0xffffffff);
1810 nvkm_wr32(device, GPC_UNIT(gpc, 0x2c94), 0xffffffff);
1811 }
1812
1813 for (rop = 0; rop < gr->rop_nr; rop++) {
1814 nvkm_wr32(device, ROP_UNIT(rop, 0x144), 0xc0000000);
1815 nvkm_wr32(device, ROP_UNIT(rop, 0x070), 0xc0000000);
1816 nvkm_wr32(device, ROP_UNIT(rop, 0x204), 0xffffffff);
1817 nvkm_wr32(device, ROP_UNIT(rop, 0x208), 0xffffffff);
1818 }
1819
1820 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400108, 0xffffffff);
1821 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400138, 0xffffffff);
1822 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400118, 0xffffffff);
1823 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400130, 0xffffffff);
1824 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x40011c, 0xffffffff);
1825 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400134, 0xffffffff);
1826
1827 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x400054, 0x34ce3464);
1828
1829 gf100_gr_zbc_init(gr);
1830
1831 return gf100_gr_init_ctxctl(gr);
1832}
